<paragraph id="8BE98519D10A496A7B04C3CDFC4136FA" blockId="19.[380,1208,571,669]" box="[634,954,642,669]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7B04C3CDFD2836FA" box="[634,723,642,668]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1737,1763]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,274,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[189,1398,268,1681]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Wing venation of the species described here. A. Belyta knudhoejgaardi sp. nov. B. Cinetus breviscapus sp. nov.C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov.D. Pantoclis globosasp. nov. E. Pantolyta augustinusii sp. nov. F. Basalys villumi sp. nov. G. Doliopria baltica sp. nov. H. Spilomicrus succinalis sp. nov. Scale bars: A–E = 1 mm; F, H = 0.5 mm; G = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468171/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Figs 1F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7BA1C3CDFCDF36FB" box="[735,804,642,669]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1778,1804]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 5. A–C. Pantolyta chemyrevae sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608448). A. Habitus in dorsolateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Petiole in lateral view. D–E. Pantolyta similis sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608468). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Mesosoma, petiole and anterior gaster in dorsal view. F–H. Basalys villumi sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608360). F. Habitus in lateral view. G. Head in lateral view. H. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mpk = median propodeal keel. Scale bars: A, D, F = 1 mm; B, E, G–H = 0.5 mm; C = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">5F–H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7A4FC3CDFCAC36FA" box="[817,855,642,668]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1780,1806]" captionTargetBox="[271,1316,265,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[271,1316,265,1743]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 6. A. Basalys villumi sp. nov., paratype (NHMD-608369), habitus in lateral view. B–D. Doliopria baltica sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608374). B. Habitus in lateral view. C. Head in lateral view. D. Mesosoma and metasoma in lateral view. E–H. Spilomicrus succinalis sp. nov. E–F. Holotype (NHMD-607131). E. Habitus in ventrolateral view. F. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. G. Paratype (NHMD-608344), habitus in lateral view. H. Paratype (NHMD-608354), habitus in lateral view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; te = tergite excision. Scale bars: A, E–H = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C–D = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468201/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">6A</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="C6D4B0A2D10A496A7A1DC3CDFC4136FA" box="[867,954,642,668]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[189,259,265,291]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Table 1. Fossil record of the Diapriidae Haliday, 1833 in Baltic amber (1 Pantolyta similis sp. nov. was originally identified as P. macrocera (Thomson, 1858))." pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Table 1</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D10A496A79C3C38CFBE537FC" pageId="19" pageNumber="76" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10A496A79C3C38CFECD36BB" blockId="19.[189,310,707,733]" box="[189,310,707,733]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">
<heading id="D0A13275D10A496A79C3C38CFECD36BB" bold="true" box="[189,310,707,733]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="76" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10A496A79C3C38CFECD36BB" bold="true" box="[189,310,707,733]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10A496A79C3C3BDFBE537FC" blockId="19.[188,1399,754,922]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">
Body smooth; scape seven times as long as wide; pedicel conical; flagellomeres cylindrical and longer than wide; F1 longest; F2–F11 similar in length; F2 conspicuously emarginate (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7D10C25AFB143756" box="[1134,1263,789,816]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1778,1804]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 5. A–C. Pantolyta chemyrevae sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608448). A. Habitus in dorsolateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Petiole in lateral view. D–E. Pantolyta similis sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608468). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Mesosoma, petiole and anterior gaster in dorsal view. F–H. Basalys villumi sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608360). F. Habitus in lateral view. G. Head in lateral view. H. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mpk = median propodeal keel. Scale bars: A, D, F = 1 mm; B, E, G–H = 0.5 mm; C = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Fig. 5D–E</figureCitation>
); scutellum subquadrate without posterior scutellar pits (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7BB8C276FCE43735" box="[710,799,824,851]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1778,1804]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 5. A–C. Pantolyta chemyrevae sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608448). A. Habitus in dorsolateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Petiole in lateral view. D–E. Pantolyta similis sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608468). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Mesosoma, petiole and anterior gaster in dorsal view. F–H. Basalys villumi sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608360). F. Habitus in lateral view. G. Head in lateral view. H. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mpk = median propodeal keel. Scale bars: A, D, F = 1 mm; B, E, G–H = 0.5 mm; C = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
); fore wing bordered with small hairs, r-rs short but distinct, M+Cu nebulous (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A788BC213FDB43710" box="[501,591,860,886]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1737,1763]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,274,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[189,1398,268,1681]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Wing venation of the species described here. A. Belyta knudhoejgaardi sp. nov. B. Cinetus breviscapus sp. nov.C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov.D. Pantoclis globosasp. nov. E. Pantolyta augustinusii sp. nov. F. Basalys villumi sp. nov. G. Doliopria baltica sp. nov. H. Spilomicrus succinalis sp. nov. Scale bars: A–E = 1 mm; F, H = 0.5 mm; G = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468171/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); hind wing narrow, two thirds of fore wing length, with long hairs along posterior margin; petiole three times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7A05C230FC2637FC" box="[891,989,895,922]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1778,1804]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[273,1315,265,1739]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 5. A–C. Pantolyta chemyrevae sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608448). A. Habitus in dorsolateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Petiole in lateral view. D–E. Pantolyta similis sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608468). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Mesosoma, petiole and anterior gaster in dorsal view. F–H. Basalys villumi sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608360). F. Habitus in lateral view. G. Head in lateral view. H. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mpk = median propodeal keel. Scale bars: A, D, F = 1 mm; B, E, G–H = 0.5 mm; C = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Figs 5D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136D999CD10A496A7A97C230FBEA37FC" box="[1001,1041,895,922]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1780,1806]" captionTargetBox="[271,1316,265,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[271,1316,265,1743]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 6. A. Basalys villumi sp. nov., paratype (NHMD-608369), habitus in lateral view. B–D. Doliopria baltica sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608374). B. Habitus in lateral view. C. Head in lateral view. D. Mesosoma and metasoma in lateral view. E–H. Spilomicrus succinalis sp. nov. E–F. Holotype (NHMD-607131). E. Habitus in ventrolateral view. F. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. G. Paratype (NHMD-608344), habitus in lateral view. H. Paratype (NHMD-608354), habitus in lateral view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; te = tergite excision. Scale bars: A, E–H = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C–D = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468201/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">6A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D10A496A79C3C28EFB39304B" pageId="19" pageNumber="76" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10A496A79C3C28EFEBF37BD" blockId="19.[189,324,961,987]" box="[189,324,961,987]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">
<heading id="D0A13275D10A496A79C3C28EFEBF37BD" bold="true" box="[189,324,961,987]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="76" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10A496A79C3C28EFEBF37BD" bold="true" box="[189,324,961,987]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10A496A79C3C2BFFB39304B" blockId="19.[189,1399,1007,1069]" pageId="19" pageNumber="76">We dedicate this species to Villum Fonden, who generously contributed to funding for purchasing the amber pieces studied. The specific epithet is to be treated as a noun in the genitive case.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
